voices.mp3Text: All hail the Lord of Trolls.
The strong shall eat the weak.
My hate shall burn you down.
All hail the Lord of Trolls.
The strong shall eat the weak.
My hate shall burn you down.
All you trolls pay attention when I tell you, this one is in the bag.
The bell tolls for the lord of trolls.
I bring out the troll in everyone.
They'll do what I tell them or regret it.
A nasty business just got nastier.
You thought I was bad before?
No last wishes, no second thoughts.
Death is my way of life.
Killing you was the least I could do.
I'll be here when you get back.
Death brings an end to pain, unfortunately.
You were a casualty of war.
Pay attention when I kill you.
Why do I enjoy this so much.
I'll pry your eyes from your skull.
Hah hah hah heh heh hah heh.
Even stone can't turn my blades.
voices.name: Tiny

voices.mp3Text: Your life is trunk-cated, heh hah he hah.
voices.name: Treant Protector

voices.mp3Text: There's no thread of yours I can't snarl up.
voices.name: Weaver

voices.mp3Text: Whatever form you take, I'll dominate it.
voices.name: Morphling

voices.mp3Text: I'll kill you again, and again, and again.
voices.name: Huskar

voices.mp3Text: You remind me of me. I hate you most of all!
voices.name: Huskar

voices.mp3Text: No suffering is enough for you.
voices.name: Dazzle

voices.mp3Text: The trolls from the hills are barely trolls at all.
voices.name: Shadow Shaman

voices.mp3Text: Hill trolls are the weakest of our kind.
voices.name: Shadow Shaman

voices.mp3Text: Your mind was not so keen as my blades.
voices.name: Tinker

voices.mp3Text: Ride your ogre to hell, small-keen.
voices.name: Alchemist

voices.mp3Text: Ogre, you had a growth on your neck. I cut it off.
voices.name: Alchemist

voices.mp3Text: I knocked that chip off your shoulder.
voices.name: Alchemist

voices.mp3Text: You keen folk cower behind your gadgets.
voices.name: Gyrocopter

voices.mp3Text: You were strong for a keen, but that's not saying much.
voices.name: Clockwerk

voices.mp3Text: Not so cheerful now, are you?
voices.name: Enchantress

voices.mp3Text: Do you know what I hate? You!
voices.name: Enchantress

voices.mp3Text: It's not the size of the axe that matters, it's how you swing it.
voices.name: Axe

voices.mp3Text: Nyaheh heh, first blood, last word, I got it all.
Let's kill these fools before we start in on each other.
I can see I'll have to carry us to victory.
I kill my enemies first, my allies next.
Would that I could fight alone.
Why are my allies so weak and pathetic?
I'd be better off fighting alone.
I'd rather strip this from a corpse.
Keep on smiling, Keeper, it won't last.
If I wanted your opinion, I wouldn't be me.
Keep on smiling, shopkeeper. It won't last.
Keep on smiling, shopkeeper. It won't last.
I'd like to fill out an application.
I'll cave in their skulls with this.
voices.name: Aghanim's Scepter (4200)

voices.mp3Text: The better to carve out their living hearts.
voices.name: Blink Dagger (2250)

voices.mp3Text: Mask of death? Are you kidding me?
voices.name: Morbid Mask (1100)

voices.mp3Text: My hate will bring me back.
Hell has no room for my kind.
With this team, I didn't have a chance!
No more playing nice, just in case you thought I was.
You can't have a war without a warlord!
The past is death, the present is death, the future, yeah, more death!
Fighting a troll only makes him grow stronger.
No more mister nice guy, and believe me, that's what I was.
This war will end when everybody's dead.
Being dead only makes me angrier.
Trolls always get the last word.
I like to bottle it up until it explodes.
Saved for later, to serve it up cold.
Anonymity, the friend to every troll.
Anonymity, the friend to every troll.
Do that again, and I will kill you.

text: Third and more attempts within 10 seconds

voices.mp3Text: Now I'm ready, to stab you.
It is time to gut you.

voices.mp3Text: Do that again, and I will kill you.
Get off your ass and help me!
I suffer the innocents and guilty alike. There are no innocents.
The strong eat the weak, and I eat the strong.
And they said I'd never survive outside my mother's den.
And they said I'd never survive outside my mother's den.
I'm not even sure why I'm so mad.
Why am I angry for no reason?
Sometimes you just wake up on the wrong side of the bed.
I'm still going to kill you later.
Next time, be quicker about it.
No, I do not do a high five.
I'm not even sure why I'm so mad.
Even with this team, I managed to win.
Don't look at me. I did everything right.
If I had a decent team, this never would have happened.
Why do I always get the worst teams?
I knew I should have gone to bed instead.
We only lost because my whole team are noobs!
Oh, I deserve this for being so nice.
I can't get any good help.
